main event: A witness in Labrador spotted an unidentified flat, white or silver, elliptical object in the sky on November 6, 1954.
interesting points: The object was approximately 25-30 feet in diameter and maintained a slow, level course across the sky.
The object suddenly accelerated and disappeared in a south-easterly direction toward the ocean.
The object did not exhibit any trails, vapors, or sounds.
The report states that the object's behavior and appearance did not match any known aircraft at the time.
sighted object: a flat, white or silver, elliptical object
